Parliament, Thursday 13 June 2019 – Parliament’s Presiding Officers, led by the National Assembly Speaker Ms Thandi Modise and National Council of Provinces Chairperson Mr Amos Masondo, will provide details about all aspects of the 6th Parliament’s State of readiness to host the State of the Nation Address (SONA) by the Head of State. The 20 June SONA is the first for the 6th Parliament of the Republic of South Africa.
	
	DETAILS OF THE MEDIA BRIEFING ARE AS FOLLOWS: 
	
	DATE: THURSDAY, 13 JUNE 2019
	TIME: 13.00
	VENUE: G26, GROUND FLOOR – NATIONAL ASSEMBLY BUILDING
	
	ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENT OF THE REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA MPs have freedom of speech in Parliament, as long as they keep within the parliamentary rules. They cannot be prosecuted, arrested, imprisoned or be expected to pay damages for anything they say, produce or submit in Parliament or its committees.Read more